    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4aa16782_da44049c",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLGLSLCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T14:44:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I was trying to be cautious here. Unfortunately, `using \u003cenum\u003e` imports the name of the enum, but *not* any values. So we\u0027d still need to prefix every kFoo_Precedence (or have a using statement per-value, which is probably worse than just being explicit everywhere).\n\nI\u0027ve changed things more dramatically, and I think the end result is much nicer:\n\n1) Made Precedence an enum class, and removed the _Precedence from each name accordingly.\n2) Added using Precedence \u003d Operators::Precedence to the class declarations.\n3) Instances of precedence values are only one char longer than before, and no `using namespace` needed.",
      "parentUuid": "ae50638d_b562ba85",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "f4c51025090359731dcc9149f51a40562081b50e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
